<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin on Russian-Belarussian Union Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The development of the
Russian-Belarussian Union should not depend on "political trends,"
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said at the meeting of
the union's Executive Committee in Minsk today.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax reported from Minsk that Chernomyrdin, who arrived
there today, said that when discussing the Russian and Belarussian
strategic interests, "we must learn to maintain calm and remember
the objective of making our cooperation more efficient."
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the two nations' efforts must be focused on the
economic sectors "ensuring the creation of a single economic space
in the long run."
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin outlined the new joint economic programs which
include developing "dual use" technologies, manufacturing
equipment for flax, and producing and processing peat.
</P>
<P>
According to him, almost 90 percent of the budget totaling 660
billion Russian rubles (110.88 million US dollars) will be
allocated for developing and implementing joint programs.
</P>
<P>
Today's committee meeting adopted a resolution on creating a
single investment space. An advisory council on investment policy
was established under the committee to pursue this objective.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the committee approved new principles for imposing
tariffs on electric and heating power to ensure stable operation
of the two countries' energy sectors. An agreement was reached on
unifying approaches to determining transportation tariffs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
