<HEADLINE> Thailand Agrees to Set Up ASEAN Foundation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government agreed here
today to sign the memorandum of understanding on the establishment
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) Foundation.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet at its weekly meeting today authorized the
Thai Foreign Ministry to join other ASEAN countries to sign the
document in Kuala Lumpur on December 14-16 this year, according to
the Thai Government House.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the foundation aims to promote the ASEAN
consciousness and create social network among ASEAN people, the
Government House said in a press release.  
</P>
</TEXT>
