<HEADLINE> Gas Explosion Leaves 61 Dead in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 61 miners were killed
in a methane gas explosion today at Zyryanovskaya coal mine in
Novokuznestk, Kemerovo region, the Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Six miners with burns and other injuries have been treated at a
local hospital, while rescue workers continue to look for the
remaining miners.
</P>
<P>
The explosion reportedly occurred in the early hours today
during the shift change while 130 people were working in the
mine. About 67 miners in coal layer number 14 were involved in the
explosion.
</P>
<P>
Many of the coal miners in other sections escaped serious
injury, the agency quoted a coal industry official as saying.
</P>
<P>
It could, however, be one of the biggest mining accidents in
Russia in decades, the official said.
</P>
<P>
According to another report, Russian President Boris Yeltsin,
who is visiting in Stockholm, sent a message of condolence to the
relatives of the coal miners killed and injured in the accident.
</P>
<P>
Excluding today's accident, 62 miners have died this year in
coal mines of the Kemerovo region, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
