<HEADLINE> Vietnam Has 40,000 Victims of Chemical Agents: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has about 40,000 victims
as a result of chemical agents that were used during the Vietnam
War which ended over 22 years ago, Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 people from 14,000 families were born deformed
because their mothers were exposed to chemical agents during the
war, according to a survey in 21 provinces and cities. Some
families reportedly had as many as seven children with deformities.
</P>
<P>
Among these people, at least 3,000 are paralyzed and 40,000
others have mental disorders.
</P>
<P>
The estimated figures were revealed by Vietnam's Ministry of
Science, Technology and Environment; the Ministry of Health; the
Ministry of Labour, War Invalids and Social Affairs, and other
relevant agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
