MOSCOW -- At least 61 miners were killed in a methane gas
explosion today at Zyryanovskaya coal mine in Novokuznestk,
Kemerovo region, the Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Six miners with burns and other injuries have been treated at a
local hospital, while rescue workers continue to look for the
remaining miners.
</P>
<P>
The explosion reportedly occurred in the early hours today
during the shift change while 130 people were working in the
mine. About 67 miners in coal layer number 14 were involved in
the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Many of the coal miners in other sections escaped serious
injury, the agency quoted a coal industry official as saying.
(Russia-Mine-Accident) 
</P>
