<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Values Ties With Latin America, says Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin called today for strengthened cooperation between China and
Latin America, saying that they share responsibilities in
promoting world peace, development and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In a speech delivered at the Mexican Senate, Jiang said, "China
has all along attached importance to the strengthening of friendly
cooperative relations with countries in Latin America and the
Caribbean, including Mexico."
</P>
<P>
"Both China and the Latin American nations are developing
countries," Jiang said. "Long histories, ancient civilizations,
similar development experiences and other common points have
closely linked us together."
</P>
<P>
He expressed his conviction that Sino-Latin American economic
and trade cooperation has broader prospects with the wider opening
up of the countries and expanding cooperation in such areas as
science and technology and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1970s, China has established diplomatic relations
with most of the Latin American countries. Friendship between them
has developed continuously with mutual understanding enhanced and
areas of cooperation expanded.
</P>
<P>
These developments, Jiang said, have laid a sound foundation
for even wider cooperation on the basis of mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Jiang came to Mexico on Saturday on a five-day state visit from
Canada, where he attended the fifth informal leaders' meeting of
the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation forum in Vancouver and then
paid a four-day state visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
