<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Cooperation Between Developed, Developing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin today called for closer cooperation between developed
and developing countries and earlier establishment of new
international political and economic orders.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at Mexico's Senate, Jiang said the
cooperation between developed and developing countries should
serve the principle of guaranteeing a fair, equal and
non-discriminatory way for the developing countries to
participate in the decision-making of the world economic operation.
</P>
<P>
The aim of such cooperation is to achieve common development
and prosperity of all the countries in the world, he added.
</P>
<P>
Developed countries should respect and take into account the
interests of the developing countries, and provide necessary
support for developing countries to achieve sustained development,
he said.
</P>
<P>
In return, the rapid economic growth in developing countries
will provide developed countries with broader markets and help
them develop sustainably at a higher level, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We should view and handle the economic relations between
developing and developed countries from such dialectical and
historic perspective," he noted.
</P>
<P>
With profound changes in the current world, maintaining peace,
seeking cooperation and promoting development have become the
major stream of the times, the Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
With the growing trend of political and economic
multipolarization in regions and the world at large, the
adjustment of relations among big powers is underway, and the
status and influence of the developing countries are
strengthening, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the old unfair and irrational international political
and economic orders are still infringing upon the interests of the
developing countries, he noted.
</P>
<P>
In the present situation, it is necessary for all the countries
in the world to promote economic cooperation and cultural
exchanges among themselves, he said.
</P>
<P>
It is the need of the times to comprehensively strengthen
South-South cooperation, improve South-North relations and
establish a fresh political and economic order in the world, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The 5th APEC informal leaders' meeting has just concluded, he
said, and the growth of APEC has been a good try for developing
and developed countries to promote economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people ardently love peace and long for
development," he said. China attaches great importance to
enhancing unity and cooperation with other developing countries.
</P>
<P>
China will as always develop its trade ties, economic and
technological cooperation and scientific and cultural exchanges
with other countries on the basis of equality and mutual benefit,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in Mexico Saturday for a five-day official
visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
