<HEADLINE> France Refuses to Back New NATO Integrated Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 2 (Xinhua) -- France today abstained from a
vote at the NATO headquarters in Brussels on introducing a new
integrated military commanding structure to the alliance, because
it is insufficient for giving more European identity to NATO,
reported Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
"We cannot associate ourselves with the decisions of approval
for the new structure, in its present state, but we guard not to
make obstacle," AFP quoted French Foreign Minister Alain Richard
as saying during a meeting with his NATO counterparts.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new structure fails to reach a new balance in
responsibilities between Europeans and Americans as France wished.
But he also said that France will continue to increase its
military activities within NATO.
</P>
<P>
"France wishes the alliance to pursue its adaptation," said
Richard in reference to a re-examination by NATO of its strategic
concept after the end of the Cold War, and the creation of an
organism in charge for carrying out peace-keeping missions within
the general staff of NATO. 
</P>
</TEXT>
