<HEADLINE> US Delegation Visits Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- An American delegation
led by congressman Tom Campbell of California arrived here
today for a four-day working visit to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to Campbell, the U.S. delegation will confer with
senior Ethiopian government officials and members of the House of
People's Representatives on the situation in the Horn of Africa,
bilateral ties, as well as issues concerning the International
Monetary Fund and the Development Bank of Africa.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a report said here today that a senior American
presidential economic delegation will shortly visit Ethiopia and
other five sub-Saharan African countries, like Eritrea, Botswana,
Mauritius, Cote d'Ivoire and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the visit is aimed at re-invigorating
the existing trade and investment relations between Washington
and the five African countries.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. economic delegation, which comprises senior U.S.
government officials and members of the U.S. business community,
will hold discussions with pertinent authorities in the African
countries on the international commercial law the U.S. is
drafting.
</P>
<P>
Besides, U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is
scheduled to visit this country on December 9 on the initial leg
of her first African tour since becoming Secretary of State.
</P>
<P>
She will address the Organization of African Unity during
her one-day stay in Ethiopia. 
</P>
