<HEADLINE> UK Army Helpline Opens to Support Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The British Army opened a
confidential helpline today for soldiers with personal problems
in an effort to eradicate racism, bullying and sexual harassment
as well as marital difficulties, child abuse or drug addiction.
</P>
<P>
Local press reports today said that the help line, which costs
250,000 pounds (425,000 US dollars) a year and staffed by 15
civilians, is part of a "caring" initiative by the army and
families of servicemen can also ring for advice.
</P>
<P>
The 15-strong staff includes specially trained experts and
ex-army personnel.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that soldiers are guaranteed absolute
confidentiality and do not give their names if they just want
advice, but the unit would supply the army with general
information about any trends that might emerge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
