<HEADLINE> 300 Ethiopians Attend German Colleges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The German Academic
Exchange Service (DAAD) has said here that it has offered 300
scholarships to Ethiopians in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to academics of the Addis Ababa University Monday,
Secretary General of the DAAD Christian Bode said Ethiopians are
now attending 100 German universities.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the German embassy
here, the DAAD offers scholarships to 80 Ethiopians annually,
spending about 17.6 million U.S. Dollars to sponsor higher
learning to Ethiopian scientists each year.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Karl Duisberg Society and the German Development
Organization also offer vocational scholarships to 50 Ethiopians
annually.
</P>
<P>
Four thousand Ethiopians have benefited from similar
scholarships in Germany over the past 10 years, according to the
press release. 
</P>
