<HEADLINE> UNITA Condemned for Laying Landmines Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The National Union for the
Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) is condemned by Angola's
joint commission for peace process here today for laying mines
again in areas cleared of mines.
</P>
<P>
David Wimhurst, spokesman for the UN Angola observation group
said that the commission has found nine cases of citizens being
injured by landmines in central Angola's Kuito City.
</P>
