total banning of anti-personnel landmines to be held in Ottawa,
capital of Canada on December 6, when more than 120 countries
would have their representatives there.
</P>
<P>
Angola is one of the countries which has most of the landmines
in the world.
</P>
<P>
UN statistics show that the country has about 10 million mines
scattered on its land.
</P>
<P>
So far, only about 5,000 landmines have been cleared and a lot
more work is required to clear the rest in the ground. 
