have been developed between NATO and Russia for the implementation
of the military aspects of the Dayton peace accord.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to draw on the practical experience gained from
Bosnia in pursuing their commitment to consultation and
cooperation in the field of crisis management and conflict
prevention in the future.
</P>
<P>
Satisfaction was shown at the meeting, according to the same
source who preferred to remain anonymous, for the steps that have
been taken to implement the 1997 NATO-Russia work program such as
the beginning of practical work in the newly established joint
working groups on peacekeeping and civil emergency planning and
disaster relief. 
