<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Both August First Rockets and
Shandong Flaming Bulls improved their unbeaten records to 4-0
after matches in the China's Basketball League on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rockets edged Beijing Ducks 88-68 (44-30) while Flaming Bulls
beat Guangdong Tigers 74-60 (36-31).
</P>
<P>
Liu Qiang scored 26 to lead Rockets to the biggest gap of 31
points in the road. Wang Zhizhi added 22 points, 13 boards and
four blocks for the defending champions.
</P>
<P>
Rockets averaged 93 points in their first four games into the
season, and held their opponents at 69.5 points per game.
</P>
<P>
Flaming Bulls, who finished fourth last season, played
spectacular openings in two occasions to made the best start in
franchise history.
</P>
<P>
Gong Xiaobin, top scorer in the first three rounds, grabbed 19
rebounds of 45 of his team, which shot 28-52 in the field.
</P>
<P>
In Shanghai, Zhejiang Squirrels beat hosts Sharks 54-53 thanks
to center Yu Leping's last-second jumper.
</P>
<P>
Hu Weidong, who was the winner of last season's Best Scorer
Award, shot 40 points and six assists to lead Jiangsu Dragons for
a 89-73 victory over runner-up Liaoning Hunters for a 2-2 match
record.
</P>
<P>
In Wednesday's other matches, Sichuan Pandas downed Shenyang
Army Lions 63-54 while Jinan Army Pegasus defeated Lianhang Eagles
72-65. 
</P>
