<HEADLINE> Asian Meeting on Interaction and Confidence Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Deputy foreign ministers from
Russia, Egypt and 14 Asian countries pledged during a one-day
meeting here today to promote political dialogues on regional
peace, security and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Participants from the 16 members of the Conference on
Interaction and Confidence-Building Measures in Asia (CICA) also
agreed to discuss disarmament on terms acceptable to all sides.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to further cooperate on science and
technology, telecommunications, energy, trade and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
They decided that foreign ministers of the CICA membership
should also meet again in 1998 or 1999.
</P>
<P>
The CICA, modeled on the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe, was proposed by Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev at the United Nations General Assembly in October 1992.
</P>
<P>
The forum now groups Afghanistan, Azerbaijan, China, Egypt,
India, Iran, Israel, Kazakhstan, Kyrghyz, Mongolia, Pakistan,
Palestine, Russia, Tajikistan, Turkey and Uzbekistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
