<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Stresses Cooperation with CIS States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin said today that Russia attaches great importance to
integrational cooperation among the Commonwealth of Independent
States (CIS).
</P>
<P>
Broad integrational cooperation with member countries of the
CIS has been and remains the top priority of Russian policy, said
Chernomyrdin at a meeting of the coordination council of
power-wielding structures in CIS countries.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin noted that this cooperation is based on similar
and various interests in economic and social development, national
security and international activity.
</P>
<P>
Russia is making efforts to ensure that integration in the
Commonwealth framework becomes part and parcel of the entire
system of economic management, Chernomyrdin said.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin has prepared a decree "on
Russia's urgent action to step up and deepen integrational
processes in the CIS," said the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The Russian government is preparing proposals and measures
relating to all aspects of an economic integrational policy.
</P>
<P>
The proposals include the coordination of structural and market
transformations, the stepping up of interstate coordination of
foreign economic activity, and perfection of balance and payment
relations, as well as the settlement of problems of debt and
harmonization of the tax policy, he added.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin indicated that the CIS summit on January 23, 1998,
"Will be a milestone in the Commonwealth development."
</P>
<P>
Russia will concentrate on creating free-trade zones in the
territories of CIS member-countries and on the development and
strengthening of the Customs Union, Chernomyrdin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
