<HEADLINE> Congresses of Non-Communist Parties And Organizations Hailed (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- "People's Daily" will carry an
editorial tomorrow to congratulate on the Congresses of
Non-Communist Parties and the All-China Federation of Industry and
Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that the meetings were held at a time when
the nation is studying and implementing the guidelines of the 15th
National Party Congress, half a century after the multi-party
co-operative system under the CPC leadership was established.
</P>
<P>
China has eight non-Communist Parties: The Revolutionary
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, the China Democratic League,
the China Democratic National Construction Association, the China
Association for Promoting Democracy, the Chinese Peasants and
Workers Democratic Party, the China Zhi Gong Party, the Jiu San
Society, and the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
This is the last national congress of these Parties and the
federation this century, it says. They worked out guidelines, set
goals, approved constitutions, elected new leaders, all of which
will be significant for developing the patriotic united front.
</P>
<P>
The meetings benefitted long-term co-operation with the CPC and
helped the country improve multi-party co-operation under CPC
leadership.
</P>
<P>
The editorial goes on to say that China's central task now and
in the coming years is to unite people with the guidelines of the
15th Party Congress and to reach goals set by the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Non-Communist parties and All-China Federation of Industry
and Commerce have studied the guidelines and their work will help
the course of building socialism with Chinese characteristics into
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
These parties and the organization will get their members to
study Deng Xiaoping Theory conscientiously, participate in and
discuss government and political affairs, and get involved in
democratic supervisory work, says the article. In this way, it
adds, they will make a greater contribution to rejuvenating and
reunifying China.
</P>
