<HEADLINE> Pak Bar Association Supports Justice Sajjad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme Court Bar
Association (SCBA) today expressed its full support for Justice
Sajjad Ali Shah whose appointment as the Chief Justice has been
suspended.
</P>
<P>
SCBA also announced that it is meeting Saturday to chalk out
its strategy for the situation arising from the ouster of the
under restraint Chief Justice Sajjad Ali Shah.
</P>
<P>
SCBA Vice President Ashraf Tanoli told the local media today
after oath-taking of Acting Chief Justice Ajmal Mian that the
members of SCBA have decided to extend full support to Justice
Sajjad.
</P>
<P>
"The Bar will stand by Justice Sajjad because of his role for
independence of judiciary which is considered to be a historical
role," said Tanoli.
</P>
<P>
He also said that SCBA will hold a meeting Saturday in which
representatives of Pakistan's all High Court bar associations will
be invited to discuss the situation arising from the ouster of
Justice Sajjad and chalk out a common strategy.  
</P>
