<HEADLINE> Preparations for Pak Presidential Polls Begin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Election
Commission has started preliminary preparations for the election
to the office of President that has fallen vacant after Farooq
Leghari's resignation Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Election Commission said that under the
Constitution, the presidential election has to be held within 30
days. The election schedule is being finalized and could be
announced anytime.
</P>
<P>
Under the Constitution, any Muslim Pakistani citizen enrolled
as a voter, not less than 45 years of age and qualified to become
a member of the National Assembly, can be elected President.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the Constitution, the electoral college for
the election of President consists of all members of the Senate,
the National Assembly and the four provincial assemblies.
</P>
</TEXT>
