<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Water Conservation Policy And The National Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Industrial Policy on
the Water Conservancy Sector, formulated by the Ministry of Water
Resources and State Planning Commission, is intended to reduce the
gap between supply and demand, make better use of water resources,
and increase the flood controls.
</P>
<P>
According to a press conference on the policy held by the State
Planning Commission today, in recent years, frequent floods have
caused enormous losses, half of China's cities face fresh water
shortages, and there are serious water pollution problems in many
provinces.
</P>
<P>
The policy has three aims: one is to determine the water
conservation projects and increase funds resources; a second is
setting water charges to make them more reasonable; and a third is
getting people to conserve fresh water and protect water resources.
</P>
<P>
Water conservation is important for basic industries and the
nation's economy, and the country needs to make better use of
water resources and put more investment into water conservation
projects.
</P>
<P>
These are divided into Type-A that have social beneficial
results and include water control, irrigation, and drainage
projects and get funding from the central and local governments,
and Type-B, with economic benefits, involving water supply,
hydro-electric, and reservoir projects, which use non-government
financing from enterprises that are responsible for their
operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Condemns Rise in Kidnapping in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today said the current rise of kidnap-for-ransom cases in the
country is "deplorable and condemnable".
</P>
<P>
"The current rise of kidnap-for-ransom cases, including the
last ones where the victims themselves were killed, is really
deplorable. It is condemnable in terms of the actions of the
perpetrators of these dastardly acts," Ramos said in his weekly
news conference.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ramos ordered Philippine National Police Director
General Recaredo Sarmiento to submit a progress report on the
police's anti-crime campaign in 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
He also summoned law enforcement agencies to "return to the
basics" of crime-fighting to "neutralize" lawless elements and tap
the community to the utmost to fight against kidnapping gangs and
other criminal syndicates.
</P>
<P>
"The community is not to be blamed here. It is the officials,
the authorities that must work extra hard, because they are
responsible at bottom line in strengthening the community
network," Ramos added.
</P>
<P>
Ramos' remarks came after five Chinese-Filipino residents were
kidnapped Tuesday in the northern Philippines amid the mounting
protest from the Chinese community against the government's
failure to curb the kidnappings.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Chinese-Filipinos Tuesday attended the funeral
protest march of the 25-year-old Gordon Tan, who was killed when
resisting his kidnappers on November 24. Chinese shops and schools
were also closed in parts of Manila in protest.
</P>
<P>
Police statistics showed that in the first 10 months of this
year, there were 124 cases of kidnapping for ransom involving 193
victims nationwide, mostly wealthy Filipino-Chinese businessmen.
</P>
</TEXT>
