<HEADLINE> Indian Govt Recommends Dissolution of Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 3 (Xinhua)-- The Union Cabinet of the
United Front (UF) government decided to recommend dissolution of
Lok Sabha (Lower House of Parliament) in its meeting here this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Home Minister Indrajit Gupta is expected to carry the cabinet
decision to President K.R. Narayanan later this evening.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Minister Chaturanan Mishra told newsmen after the
cabinet meeting that the decision to recommend dissolution was
unanimous.
</P>
<P>
A last-ditch effort for a compromise between the UF and
Congress by keeping the Dravida Kunnetra Kazhagam (DMK), one of
the UF constituents, failed with the Front leadership ruling out
such a possibility.
</P>
<P>
The Congress insisted on demanding removal of the DMK from the
UF government for its indictment in the Jain Commission interim
report on former prime minister Rajiv Gandhi's assassination in
1991.
</P>
<P>
The Gujral government did not recommend dissolution of the
Lower House when it tendered its resignation following the
withdrawal of support to it by the Congress on November 28.
</P>
