a 26.3 million-U.S.-dollar agreement to fund medical equipment
for the Beirut University Medical Center, local newspapers
reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said that so far, the bank has granted a total of
192.8 million U.S. dollars loans distributed among the country's
electricity, health, education and telecommunication sectors.
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese tobacco growers in the Bekaa, the main
Tobacco growing province in western Lebanon, have called on the
government to increase quotas and prices for this year's crop,
citing rising costs in the sector.
</P>
<P>
According to local newspapers, the growers in Bekaa asked to
raise the quota associated with each tobacco-growing license from
250 kilograms to 350 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
They also demanded an increase in the general production level
in the region from 2 million kilograms to 2.5 million kilograms.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel Aircraft Industries and other two Israeli
companies, Elbit and El-Op, have formed a consortium which will
offer upgrading services for F-16 jets to the Israeli Air Force
and foreign customers, Israel Business reported in its latest
issue.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Israeli government is to help finance a project
involving the construction of an enhanced prototype of the F-16
with the actual production work being carried out by the three
members of the new consortium. 
