<HEADLINE> Electronic Atlas of China Available </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- An electronic atlas of China
has been produced by the China Map Publishing House on a single
CD-ROM, according to the State Bureau of Surveying and
Mapping.
</P>
<P>
The atlas covers all provinces, autonomous regions, municipal
cities, and the Hong Kong Special Administration Region. It also
consists of maps of provincial cities and scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
More than 260 maps are included in the atlas, which provides
information on China's administrative regions, ethnic groups,
topography, climate, traffic, cultural relics and artifacts.
</P>
<P>
With multi-media technologies applied, users can perform
multi-functional tasks on the atlas such as searching for
information, viewing pictures, playing music and printing. 
</P>
