<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Ensured Berth in World Volleyball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Italy has
secured an automatic berth for the Men's World Volleyball League
slated from May 15 to July 19 next year, the International
Volleyball Federation (FIVB) said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Twelve teams will compete in three qualifying tournaments till
June 21, which features the home-and-away format.
</P>
<P>
New time-limited system will be adopted in the league wherein
either side will score one point after a regular 25 minutes and
the winners will be the first to score 15 points or a two-point
lead from a 14-all tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
The system had been first introduced in the Intercontinental
Championship Cup in Japan.
</P>
<P>
For the preliminaries, Group A has four members of Spain, Cuba,
South Korea and Bulgaria, Group B brackets Italy, Argentina, the
Netherlands and Greece while Group C pits together China, Russia,
Yoguslavia and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Apart from reigning champion and host Italy, seven best teams
from the qualifying groups will compete for other three berths in
the finals through competitions either in Spain or Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Among the seven squads, four will compete in Spain for two
final spots while other three vie in Yugoslavia for the other
ticket.
</P>
<P>
The league finals will be held in Italy on July 18 and 19.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
