<HEADLINE> Sporting Lisbon Hires Former Chilean National Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Struggling Sports Lisbon signed
a two-year contract with Vicente Cantatore, former Chilean
national coach, the Portuguese club said late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Argentinian-born coach will take over Sporting on Monday,
that has been without a coach for a month when Octavio Machado
quit on November 2 after a sad opening in the Portuguese first
division.
</P>
<P>
The club lost to lowly Leca last weekend with a record of four
wins, five draws and two losses and slid to fifth on the table.
</P>
<P>
It has also been kicked out of the quarterfinals of the
European Championships League after its defeat of 3-2 by Monaca
last week.
</P>
<P>
The 61-year-old Cantatore, who coached Chilean national soccer
team in 1979-80, made Cobreola Chile's double title-holder before
he led Spanish club Valladolid to a UEFA Cup place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
