<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 13:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting: Israel Biggest Threat to Islamic World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Islamic countries regard
Israel as the biggest threat to the Islamic world due to its
aggressive policies, Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Mohammad
Javad Zarif said here today.
</P>
<P>
As spokesman for the eighth summit of the Organization of
Islamic Conference (OIC) to be held here December 9-11, Zarif told
reporters that the on-going OIC experts meeting reached the
conclusion that Israel poses the biggest threat to the Islamic
world.
</P>
<P>
Zarif said that the issue of Middle East peace process was one
of the hot topics discussed by experts, and participants of the
meeting believed that the Middle East crisis could be resolved
only through the full restoration of the rights of the Palestinian
people.
</P>
<P>
"This is the stance taken by the Islamic Republic of Iran," he
said, adding that the Middle East peace process would remain
deadlocked if the problems of the Palestinian people are unsolved.
</P>
<P>
Iran believes that the Palestinian people should have the
right to determine their own fate, terming the repatriation of
the Palestinian refugees to their hometowns, the return of the
occupied land including Jerusalem, southern Lebanon and the Syrian
Golan heights as the main topics of the Middle East peace
process, he said.
</P>
<P>
With the consideration of the current situation in the Middle
East, Zarif said, the Islamic countries called for a lasting peace
and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
About the works of the OIC experts meeting, Zarif said that so
far the participants have reached agreements on the agendas for
the meeting of OIC foreign ministers and the OIC summit.
</P>
<P>
About 30 draft resolutions were adopted so far, he said,
mainly on the issues of Cyprus, Kashmir, Bosnia-herzegovina,
rights of children in Islamic countries, rights of women and
supports for the Muslim minorities in non-Islamic countries.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the crisis in Afghanistan, Zarif said that the
OIC experts meeting reiterated to recognize the government of
President Burhanuddin Rabbani as the sole legal government in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran and Pakistan have jointly raised a proposal
for the OIC summit and the United Nations also proposed a
recommendation for cooperation of Afghanistan's neighboring
countries to restore peace in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
About the issue of Bosnia-herzegovina, Zarif said that the
most important issue in the view of the OIC members was the
implementation of all resolutions concerning the establishment of
peace and stability in the Balkan region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
