<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The annual search and rescue
exercise, organized by the local Civil Aviation Department (CAD),
started here today to offer training and familiarization in search
and rescue techniques.
</P>
<P>
The three-day exercise this year consists of a static display
of a Super King Air and Sikorsky helicopters of the Hong Kong
Government Flying Service and search and rescue aircraft from the
United States, a long-range exercise in the South China Sea and a
symposium.
</P>
