<HEADLINE> Artists Called on to Create Better Works </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Ding Guangen, head of the
Propaganda Department of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee, told a group of artists at a China Federation of
Literary and Art Circles forum in Beijing today that artists need
to create works of art that serve the people and socialism.
</P>
<P>
Art is an important part of revolutionary development, he said,
and the first task of artists is to implement the policies of the
15th National Party Congress and to use Deng Xiaoping Theory to
create fine works of art.
</P>
<P>
Ding said that artists must follow the principle of serving the
people and socialism and letting a hundred flowers blossom and a
hundred of schools of thought contend.
</P>
<P>
He said that society must be put first in culture and the arts
and artists' work honored and artistic democracy promoted. The
masses are the key to a robust culture and artists should reflect
their heroic deeds and the reforms, opening up and moderization.
</P>
<P>
He called on artists to produce works of art that celebrate the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China
in 1999, because artists are the "engineers of the human soul" and
should study hard, read more, and improve themselves. 
</P>
