<HEADLINE> Xiang Nan's Remains Cremated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The remains of Xiang Nan, a
former member of the Central Advisory Commission of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) who died of a heart attack on November 10 in
Beijing, were cremated today.
</P>
<P>
Xiang, who was 79, had been the First Secretary of the CPC
Committee of east China's Fujian Province and the first political
commissar of the Fujian Military Area Command
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji,
Li Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing, Li Lanqing, and
Rong Yiren all expressed their condolences today over the passing
of Xiang.
</P>
<P>
He joined the CPC in 1938 and served in many Party posts during
his lifetime. Throughout his life he remained a loyal Party
member, even when he was persecuted during the Cultural Revolution
(1966-76). He was present at the 15th National Party Congress held
in September this year as a nonvoting delegate.  
</P>
