<HEADLINE> Nominations for Local Elections to Begin in Sri </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Nominations for general
elections to municipal, urban and village councils in Jaffna and
Kilinochchi districts, Northern Sri Lanka, will soon begin, a
government official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner of Elections Dayananda Dissanayake said in a press
release this afternoon that nominations of candidates for the
elections will be received from December 16 to 23.
</P>
<P>
Deposits from independent groups will be received up to 12:00
on December 22, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka held its local elections in all but the Northern
province and parts of the Eastern province in March. The polls had
been scheduled for 1995, but were postponed twice due to security
reasons.
</P>
<P>
A 14-year-long civil war is going on between government troops
and the Tamil rebels in the north and east of the country.
</P>
<P>
The nominations come at a time when troops of Operation
Jayasikuru (Certain Victory) are advancing further to the north in
their final phase of offensives.
</P>
<P>
The press release did not say when the elections will be held.
</P>
