<HEADLINE> Macao Property Trade Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that a total of 9,312 contracts of property trade were signed
during the first nine months, down 13.5 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
But those contracts involved 8,637.30 million patacas (1,093.3
million U.S. dollars), up 73.7 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, mortgage loans contracts signed during the period
involved 5,886.70 million patacas (745.15 million U.S. dollars),
up 58.1 percent. Most of the loans were for buying of house.
</P>
<P>
The real estate market in Macao has remained sluggish for
three years, with about 30,000 sets of units still waiting for
buyers. But transactions started to pick up a little since late
last year as price hit the lowest in the past ten years.
</P>
