<HEADLINE> Asian Countries Discuss Cooperation Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Officials from 16 Asian
countries began a meeting here today to discuss measures to
promote mutual trust and cooperation among them.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting, Kazakh Foreign Minister Kasymzhomart
Tokayev said that a system of dialogue and cooperation should be
established in Asia to guarantee the region's stability and
continued development in the next century.
</P>
<P>
He said such a system is essential because conflicts still
exist in Asia and many countries are divergent on issues such as
arms control and disarmament.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was first proposed by Kazakhstan President
Nursultan Nazarbayev at the 47 U.N. General Assembly in 1992.
