<HEADLINE> Share Prices Down Slightly on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices almost stayed
steady on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index (STII) lowered slightly by 0.97 points to close
at 1696.29 today.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the share prices were mixed as the market
needs to take a rest after being firm in the past two days. "But
we could see the buying come in again as people window-dress their
accounts before the end of the year," one broker said.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 167.53 million units, worth 324.83
million Singapore dollars (about 203.02 million U.S. dollars).
Advances continued to lead declines by 180 to 142, while 295 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 10.93 million units. It was followed by
Asia Food &AMP; Property which had 9.64 million shares traded. Hotung
was next with 7.4 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer maker IPCO led the gainers of the day as it rose
by 56 cents to finish at 3.06 U.S. dollars. City Development
Warrant98 increased by 35 cents to end at 5.5 Singapore dollars.
BerLand picked up 22 cents to close at 1.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, computer sound card maker Creative 50 was the
biggest loser as it declined sharply by four dollars to end at
37.1 Singapore dollars. Kulim Malaysia fell by 52 cents to close
at 1.42 Singapore dollars, while the Singapore Press Holdings
(SPH) Foreign lost 50 cents to finish at 22.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
