<HEADLINE> Three More EU Countries Grant Single Visas for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Three European Union (EU)
member countries -- Austria, Greece and Italy, have joined other
EU members to grant single visa for Ugandan businessmen or
tourists to visit their countries, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a press release by French Embassy as saying
that the decision by the three countries took effect from
December 1.
</P>
<P>
Besides the three countries, Ugandans now have access to seven
EU countries, namely France, Belgium, the Netherlands, Germany,
Luxemburg, Spain and Portugal, by using a single visa in
accordance with Sebengen Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The agreement signed on March 24, 1995 is intended to improve
relationship between Uganda and the EU, said the press release
</P>
<P>
Ugandan visitors to other EU countries such as Britain,
Denmark, Sweden, Finland and Ireland, still have to obtain visas
from the respective governments. 
</P>
