<HEADLINE> 11 Crime Suspects Escape from Kampala Police Cell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Eleven crime suspects held in
a police cell in the Ugandan capital made their escape Tuesday
night, " The New Vision" reported today, quoting a police officer.
</P>
<P>
Confirming the escape, police officer James Ocaya said: "They
seem to have taken the advantage of the morning drizzle to escape."
</P>
<P>
The officer attributed the incident to poor structure of the
cell.
</P>
<P>
The suspects held for robbery and theft, tore down some bricks
from the wall and broke through it with the help of an iron bar.
</P>
<P>
The eleven people were not the first to escape from the cell.
</P>
<P>
A strong police cell under construction will soon handed
over to the police, Ocaya noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
