<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Cabinet Expanded with New Partner's Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Surya
Bahadur Thapa today expanded his cabinet to 47 members in a
reshuffle which brought the Nepali Congress (NC) into the present
coalition.
</P>
<P>
In the reshuffle, cabinet portfolios were re-allocated among
the prime minister's National Democratic Party (RPP), the NC and
the Nepal Sadbhavana Party (NSP).
</P>
<P>
According to a notice issued by the King's Principal Press
Secretariat, the 47-member new cabinet also included five
independents.
</P>
<P>
The NC, which toppled the former coalition government on
October 4 with the support of the RPP's Thapa faction and decided
to enter the new government in late October, shared a total of 23
portfolios including home, information and communications
ministers while the RPP held 17 posts including the key ones of
finance, defense, foreign affairs and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The NSP was given the posts of local development and forestry
ministers.
</P>
<P>
It is widely believed that the NC delayed its entrance mainly
due to differences with the RPP over the allocations of
portfolios.
</P>
<P>
Though Thapa, who is also president of the RPP, had agreed to
take only nine cabinet posts for his party, his followers have
snatched 21 portfolios after the first cabinet expansion on
October 13. And worse still, they are reluctant to vacate their
seats.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Thapa had mulled over splitting some
ministries to create more posts to maintain a balance between the
ruling partners, which is crucial to his coalition survival.
</P>
<P>
However, the idea came under attack from administrative
experts, who said that the expanding government will only lead to
waste and ill coordination.
</P>
<P>
Adding more ministries to appease supporters is not novel in
Nepali politics. Former Prime Minister Sher Bahadur Deuba once
added five ministries for his disparate coalition partners,
swelling his cabinet to a record of 48 members.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that under agreements, leadership of the coalition
government will be shared by the NC and the RPP, and Thapa will
hand over the leadership 10 months after taking over as prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
Today's move is believed to get the NC ready for general
elections scheduled for 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liquid Crystal Producer Among World's Top Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 3 (Xinhua) -- A liquid crystal
manufacturer in Shijiazhuang, capital of north China's Hebei
Province, is responsible for 20 percent of the world's total by
annually producing 6,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghua Liquid Crystal Material Factory of Shijiazhuang,
with technological support from Qinghua University in Beijing, has
become one of the top three liquid crystal producers in the world.
</P>
<P>
The price of its products is a third that of imported ones. The
products occupy 70 percent of the domestic market and are also
sold overseas.
</P>
<P>
Experts in China's Ministry of Electronics Industry say the
success of the Qinghua factory has strongly enhanced the
development of China's manufacturing of liquid crystal indicators
and related materials.
</P>
<P>
The largest production lines in China for twisted liquid
crystal indicators and for glass board indicators have been
completed in Hebei.
</P>
<P>
Liquid crystal materials are key components in electronic
products such as computers, pagers and video compact discs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
