<HEADLINE> South China Launches Care Project for Elderly People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, this year began implementing the
Songbai (pine and cypress) Project to care for elderly people and
guarantee their standard of living.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 50,000 retired workers, equal to 24.5
percent of the city's work force, and 5,000 of them have no
children to provide support.
</P>
<P>
Concrete measures include ensuring that the elderly get the
same salary monthly from the insurance companies as they did
before retirement as long as they have paid the five-year
insurance fee.
</P>
<P>
Local officials believe it is advantageous to care for the
elderly in their own homes with volunteer support to combat
loneliness.
</P>
<P>
At least 10 college students volunteered to help widows and
widowers on the day when the project was launched. A month later,
there were about 300 citizens working as volunteers. A number of
enterprises offered to help fund the project.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that China is an aging society which will require
solutions to elderly issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
