<HEADLINE> Brewer Wins IBF Super Middleweight Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Charles Brewer of
Philadelphia defeated Joey DeGrandis Tuesday night to retain his
International Boxing Federation (IBF) super middleweight title.
</P>
<P>
The unanimous decision improved Brewer's record to 30-5, while
DeGrandis dropped to 23-4.
</P>
<P>
One referee scored the fight 117-111 for Brewer; the second
gave the bout to him 120-108; and the third scored it 119-109 in
favor of Brewer.
</P>
<P>
There were no knockdowns in the 12-round fight. Brewer came to
his best round in the sixth as he pelted DeGrandis, 168 pounds
(76.2kilos), with tough uppercuts and shots to the body.
</P>
<P>
It was the first title defence for Brewer who won the title on
June 21 in Tampa, Florida, when he knocked out Gary Ballard of
South Africa in five rounds.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier light heavyweight bout, 1996 U.S. Olympic bronze
medalist Antonio Tarver from Florida beat Roy Francis of New York
City in the second round, raising his record to 7-0, and the loser
fell to 5-5-3. 
</P>
