<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronology of CHT Peace Process (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The peace agreement was signed
Tuesday after a long history of blood conflict, guerrilla warfare
and a protracted peace process that took place in past two
decades.
</P>
<P>
Following is the chronology of some important events of the two
decade-old Chittagong Hill Tracks (CHT) problem and the peace
process:
</P>
<P>
1972
</P>
<P>
Jun. 24 -- A regional political party styled as "Parbatya
Chattagram Sanghati Dal" formed to realize the demand of regional
autonomy for Larma tribe.
</P>
<P>
1973
</P>
<P>
Jan. 7 -- "Shantibahini" formed as the military front of the
parbatya Chattagram Jana Sanghati Samity (PCJSS) with the
leadership of Shantu Larma.
</P>
<P>
Feb. 13 -- During a visit to the CHT, Bangabandhu Sheikh
Mujibur Rahman announced "from now on, everybody including the
tribals will be called as Bangalee".
</P>
<P>
1975
</P>
<P>
After the assassination of Bangabandhu, Shantu larma went into
hide.
</P>
<P>
1976
</P>
<P>
CHT Development Board formed. Non-tribals rehabilitated in the
CHT under government initiative.
</P>
<P>
1977
</P>
<P>
May 29 -- A major attack by Shantibahini on troops. Strength of
army beefed up.
</P>
<P>
1980
</P>
<P>
Mar.25 -- 300 killed in firing in a Buddhist Monastery at
kalampati. Shantibahini held army responsible for the killing.
</P>
<P>
1982
</P>
<P>
Oct.24 -- Jana Sanghati Samity split into two factions led
respectively by Manabendra Narayan Larma and Priti Kumar Chakma.
</P>
<P>
1983
</P>
<P>
Oct.1 -- Ershad government declared general mercy for the
members of Shantibahini.
</P>
<P>
Nov.10 -- MN Larma killed in tribal feud.
</P>
<P>
1985
</P>
<P>
Apr.19 -- many members of Priti group of Shantibahini
surrendered to the government. Priti went into hide.
</P>
<P>
Oct.21 -- first meeting between the Ershd government and PCJSS.
</P>
<P>
1987
</P>
<P>
Dec.18 -- 2nd round meeting between the Jatiya Party (JP)
government and PCJSS.
</P>
<P>
1988
</P>
<P>
Jan.24-25 -- 3rd meeting between the JP government and PCJSS.
</P>
<P>
Feb.17-18 -- 4th meeting between the JP government and PCJSS.
</P>
<P>
Jun.19 -- Fifth meeting between the JP government and PCJSS.
</P>
<P>
Dec.14-15 -- 6th meeting between the JP government and PCJSS.
</P>
<P>
1989
</P>
<P>
Feb.15 -- CHT Local Government Bill passed in the Parliament.
</P>
<P>
May 4 -- Armed attack by Shantibahini. Some tribal villages
torched allegedly by non-tribals at Longadu.
</P>
<P>
Jun.25 -- Local government election held in the CHT.
</P>
<P>
1992
</P>
<P>
Apr.10 -- 300 killed in armed clashes between tribal and
non-tribals at Village Lodang. An inquiry committee formed by the
Khaleda Zia government.
</P>
<P>
Jul.10 -- government formed a committee on CHT headed by
Communications Minister Oli Ahmed. Three local governments
rejected the committee.
</P>
<P>
Aug.1 -- PCJSS declared truce. Since then, the truce was
extended for 35 occasions. The present truce is till December
1997.
</P>
<P>
Nov.5 -- 1st meeting between BNP (Bangladesh Nationalist Party)
government and PCJSS leader Shantu Larma.
</P>
<P>
Nov.17 -- Naniarchar killing. 90 tribals killed. Another
inquiry committee formed.
</P>
<P>
Dec.26 -- 2nd meeting between the BNP government and PCJSS at
khagrachhari Circuit House.
More

=12030645
NNNN
14:50 14:51 g # HAB
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Importing More Key Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Since the beginning of the
year, Shanghai has been importing more equipment featuring 1990s
technology from developed countries to improve the competitiveness
of local products in the international market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Shanghai imported 727 million U.S. dollars
worth of technologies and equipment from January to September, a
rise of 20 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Key equipment imported accounted for 657 million U.S. dollars,
90 percent of imports for the January-September period.
</P>
<P>
Baoshan Iron and Steel Company, which is now going all out in
constructing its third phase of expansion, is a major importer of
technology and equipment. In the first nine months this year,
Baoshan imported 465 million U.S. dollars worth of technologies
and equipment, up 76 percent from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Municipal works, transportation, posts and telecommunications
are also main recipients of imported equipment and
technologies. Major imports this year in Shanghai include 55
million U.S. dollars worth of subway equipment from the United
States and mobile telecommunications networks worth 18 million
U.S. dollars from Finland.
</P>
<P>
While continuing to increase technology and equipment imports
next year, Shanghai will make a greater effort to absorb the
imported technologies and improve the quality of its products,
said local officials, adding that they hoped the imports would
help increase the city's output value, pre-tax profits and export
volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Spillway Dam Insured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Property Co. of People's
Insurance Company of China (PICC) issued a 4.02 billion yuan
policy on Monday for the construction of the spillway for the
Three Gorges Power Project.
</P>
<P>
The policy was granted to the China Yangtze Three Gorges
Project Development Corp at Sandouping, the construction site of
the project. The policy is the largest-ever insurance contract
covering construction of a hydropower project in China.
</P>
<P>
The policy calls for the insurance company to pay compensation
for losses resulting from natural disasters and accidents during
the construction period.
</P>
<P>
PICC Property Co., the primary insurance underwriter for the
Three Gorges Power Project, has formed a special professional team
to provide better services to the project.
</P>
<P>
The company has insured 134 Three Gorges construction projects,
with total premiums of over 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Three Gorges project commenced in 1993 and
is scheduled for completion in 2009. The project, which will
built in three stages, will be completed at an estimated
cost of 200 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first-phase project was completed on November 8 with the
the successful damming of the Yangtze River. Second phase
construction, which will include the spillway, the generator room
and related auxiliary facilities, is scheduled for completion in
2003, with the first generator expected to go on line in that
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
