<HEADLINE> PLA Recruits College Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 236 college graduates from
Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, had been
enlisted for military service by the end of November, an increase
of 120 enlistees on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
An official from the People's Liberation Army (PLA) recruiting
center said the city government has adopted favorable policies for
college graduates entering the military, including larger
subsidies, higher ranks and priority employment opportunities
after their enlistment period.
</P>
<P>
The chance to realize a dream of becoming a soldier and
relieving pressures accompanied with finding a job after
graduation were also factors contributing to the rising number of
college graduates opting to enlist in the military, according to
today's China Youth Daily.
</P>
<P>
The PLA has recruited more than 630 college graduates from
across the country over the past 11 months and plans to raise
significantly the number during 1998. 
