<HEADLINE> Tibet Completes Direct Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region has
successfully completed elections of deputies to people's
congresses at the township and county levels, with more than 7,000
deputies selected during direct elections.
</P>
<P>
"The election proceeded smoothly and was conducted in strict
accordance with the law," according to Pasang Norbu, director of
the Regional Government Election Office.
</P>
<P>
"Candidates nominated directly by electors were treated equally
with those selected by political parties, institutions or
organizations, and people were allowed complete freedom of choice
in the selection process," said Pasang, adding that electors
nominated 80 percent of candidates in some areas.
</P>
<P>
Deputies from ethnic minority groups accounted for some 80
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-three counties and over 900 townships attempted to
facilitate the election process by either forming election
committees or special work teams to train some 4,000 election
officials.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the regional government dispatched more than 3,000
officials to electoral districts to answer questions and encourage
people to fully exercise their democratic rights.
</P>
<P>
Pasang noted that the record turnout of eligible voters
exceeded 90 percent.
</P>
<P>
Deputies will elect officials to governments at the city and
county levels by the end of this year, and elections for the new
term regional government is scheduled for completion before May
next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
