<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Becomes National Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Stock Exchange in
south China, which recently celebrated its seventh anniversary,
has been designated as a national market.
</P>
<P>
The market has listed 359 companies over the past seven years,
with total share capital surpassing 88 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The number of listed companies on the market has increased
59-fold over the seven-year period, with share capital growing at
a rate of well over 200 percent annually and annual stock turnover
soaring by 280 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover for stock and capital hit 1.669 trillion
yuan for the January-November period this year, and accounted for
55.71 percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Some 16 million investors have opened stock trading accounts at
the Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the exchange has also introduced state-of-the-art
trade and settlement systems has led to a substantial reduction in
trading costs for investors.
</P>
<P>
An in-time market surveillance and risk prevention system is
also in place, and the exchange continues to make every effort to
standardize the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
