<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Population Growth Slows in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
recorded a declining population growth rate since introduction of
the Family Planning Policy in 1978.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the period between 1994-1996 show that the
province's birth rate fell below the national average to a level
of less than 17 per thousand, with the mortality rate falling from
seven to six per thousand.
</P>
<P>
The province's natural population increase ratio was less than
10 per thousand for the period between 1994-1996.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has also extended great effort to promote the nine-year
compulsory education program, with the illiteracy rate for young
people dropping from six percent to four percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
