<HEADLINE> Shanghai Builds More Vegetable Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is speeding up
construction of vegetable markets to meet the increasing
demand of local citizens.
</P>
<P>
Three vegetable wholesales markets are now under construction
in the city. One of them is expected to have a daily transaction
volume of more than 1,000 tons, the second will have an expected daily
business volume of more than 400 tons, and the third will be an
exchange center in the Pudong Area.
</P>
<P>
At present, 23 vegetable wholesales markets in suburban Shanghai
sell 824,000 tons of vegetables annually with a business value of
2 billion yuan (250 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The city's 117 chain stores and 23 supermarkets all sell
vegetables.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents eat more than 2 million tons of vegetables
every year, according to statistics.  
