<HEADLINE> China Records Best Cotton Purchase in Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- China had completed a cotton
purchase volume of more than 2.58 million tons by Nov. 25, this
year, a record high for the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the All-China Federation of Supply and Marketing
Cooperatives say that major cotton producers, such as Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region and Hubei, Hunan and Henan provinces, all
reported a higher cotton purchase than the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Dafeng County in Jiangsu Province ranked first in China's
county-level cotton purchase, exceeding 50,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
This year's cotton harvest was earlier than last year's. The
massive purchase process in key cotton-producing provinces and
autonomous regions began in September.
</P>
<P>
As the largest cotton producer, Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region expanded its cotton production acreage to 956,000 hectares
this year, an increase of 78,666 hectares. The region harvested
868,000 tons of cotton as against 782,000 tons last year.
</P>
<P>
According to estimates by specialists, Xinjiang's cotton output
is expected to reach 1.15 million tons by the end of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
