<HEADLINE> Hainan Sets Minimum Prices for Overseas Tours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hainan Province
has set minimum prices for overseas tours in a bid to
avoid the unfair competition resulting from lower than average
fares.
</P>
<P>
The minimum price for an eight-day tour from Hainan to Thailand
has been set at 4,000 HK dollars per person. The per person price
for a 10-day Thailand-Hong Kong tour has been set at 7,200 HK
dollars, while that for a 14-day Singapore-Malaysia-Thailand tour
is at 10,600 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The above prices include the fees for passports, visas, airport
taxes and plane tickets.  
