<HEADLINE> China Expects Accelerated Sales of Consumer Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The sales volume for consumer
goods is expected to grow during the fourth quarter this year,
according to today's China Securities.
</P>
<P>
Projections call for the retail sales volume to register an
annual growth of 10.7 percent and hit 708.4 billion yuan during
the next four months, up 9.7 percent on the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the likelihood of accelerated growth in
sales of consumer goods to a substantial reduction in import
tariffs on October 1, and a recent cut in bank interest rates.
</P>
<P>
"Tariff reductions will promote a prosperous consumer goods
market by stimulating the export sector and will lead to lower
production costs for domestic goods," according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Lower bank interest rates are also expected to boost the
consumer goods market. The consumption index for the next three
months is expected to rise 1.85 percentage points. 
