<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Yields Notable Results in Anti-Drug Battle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, has yielded notable results in its
anti-drug battle.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city in the past five years
prosecuted over 6,200 drug trafficking or using cases,
confiscating 1,400 kg of heroin and 280 kg of the drug known as
"ice".
</P>
<P>
Some 46,800 drug addicts and sellers were punished during the
crackdown.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has established anti-drug offices in the governments
at various levels, with the city government allocating special
funding for publicity programs and related work.  
</P>
</TEXT>
