<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Americas Finance Ministers Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The finance ministers of the
American countries gathered here today to discuss ways to achieve
steady development of the regional economies in a globalized world.
</P>
<P>
At the two-day forum, the participants from 34 countries will
analyze recent economic crises, macro economic stability, and
modernization and integration of financial markets.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Finance Minister Eduardo Aninat said the Asian markets'
crisis has exerted a smaller impact on the Americas than the
Mexican crisis in 1994 did .
</P>
<P>
Aninat said the regional resistance to an international crisis
was due to the establishment of sensible and cautious fiscal and
currency policies.
</P>
<P>
He said the average inflation rate in the region will be a
one-digit figure for 1997 and foreign currency exchanges will
remain stable.
</P>
<P>
Conclusions drawn at the forum will be analyzed at the coming
summit of the Americas which is to be held in Santiago in April,
1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
