<HEADLINE> Sweden, Russia Sign Eight Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Sweden and Russia forged
eight agreements Tuesday on the first day of President Boris
Yeltsin's visit to the Scandinavian nation.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the two countries signed accords on increased
cooperation to fight economic crimes, increased space cooperation,
and judicial and law enforcement cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Other documents are about nuclear safety, culture exchange
programs and Russia's repayment for the former Soviet Union's debt.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, here to discuss economic cooperation and a proposed
Baltic security pact, was joined by Swedish Prime Minister Goeran
Persson at a ceremony for signing these agreements.
</P>
<P>
His three-day state visit is the first to Sweden by a
Russian head of state since 1909. 
</P>
</TEXT>
