<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia to Boost Trade Ties With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav Prime Minister Radoje
kontic said today his Russia tour aims to give new impetus to
Yugoslavia-Russia trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Kontic left today for Russia on a two-day official visit at the
head of a government delegation and some 40 entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters at the airport that Russia has become the
first trade partner of Yugoslavia since the United Nations
Security Council lifted economic sanctions against the Balkan
country, adding that the two countries have a huge trade potential.
</P>
<P>
Last year trade turnover between Yugoslavia and Russia amounted
to 800 million U.S. dollars and it will be expected to reach 1
billion dollars this year, according to Kontic.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav prime minister said he will clinch a series of
measures with his Russian counterpart Viktor Chernomyrdin in a bid
to expand bilateral economic and trade cooperation. He predicted
the trade volume between the two countries will reach two billion
dollars at the end of the century. 
