<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Czech AIDS Rate Among the Lowest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 2 (Xinhua) -- 13 AIDS sufferers among the
total of 17 patients in the Czech Republic had died by the end of
October, according to statistics from the Czech health
administration.
</P>
<P>
During the first ten months of this year, 84 Czechs were
registered as carriers of the AIDS virus and 17 of them became the
full-blown Aids patients.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, no case of mother-to-child cross infection had been
found, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The infection rate in the country stands at a lower level among
the central eastern European countries, and for this credit is
given to measures adopted by the government.
</P>
<P>
The Czech government has given great attention to anti-AIDS
work. Since 1993, it has allocated several millions of crowns in
preventing and controlling the work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
