<HEADLINE> Colombia Fixes Prices Over Christmas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Colombia today
established fixed prices to be in force until January 15, 1998 for
25 household consumption goods.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture and the Supply Corporation of
Colombia signed the accord to avoid speculation in the market
during the Christmas season.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Minister Antonio Gomez Merlano said the move
"is a compromise of the suppliers with the government and above
all, with consumers."
</P>
<P>
He said the accord includes only non-perishable goods, because
perishables must be left to the forces of the free market. 
