<HEADLINE> China Can Feed Itself: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- China will be fully capable of
feeding itself by the year 2030 when the country's population is
expected to reach a maximum of 1.6 billion people, according to a
recent report in Economic Daily.
</P>
<P>
The daily said the projected annual per capita grain demand of
400 kg will require China to produce 650 million tons of grain
annually by 2030.
</P>
<P>
The report explained that the country will be required to
produce additional 160 million tons of grain on the basis of the
490 million ton output figure for 1996.
</P>
<P>
However, China is fully confident that it can increase grain
production by 160 million tons annually by the year 2030 through
optimizing the use of agricultural resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
