<HEADLINE> Chinese Teachers Enjoy Improved Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING. December 3 (Xinhua) -- China had allocated 45.6
billion yuan between 1992-1996 to construct apartments
with a floor space of 76.78 million sq. m. for teachers.
</P>
<P>
The massive construction program had raised the per-capita
living space for teachers from 6.6 sq. m. in 1992 to an average
8.4 sq. m. by the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the State Education Commission noted that
improved living conditions for teachers resulted from the
effective implementation of a State Council's decision in 1992 to
resolve related housing problems.
</P>
<P>
The current per capita living space for primary and middle
school teachers averages 8.5 sq. m, with the minimum figure for
college teachers standing at 7.6 square meters. 
</P>
