<HEADLINE> Spanish-Franco Summit Discusses EU Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A two-day Spanish-Franco
summit ended today in the western Spanish town of Salamanca with
its focus on the construction of Europe and the fight against
terrorism on their border areas.
</P>
<P>
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar and French President
Jacques Chirac, French Pime Minister Lionel Jospin were joined by
ministers concerned from the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of European construction, the two sides expressed
their concern over the financial future resulting from the
European Union's east expansion.
</P>
<P>
Aznar indicated he was concerned that the expansion might lead
to an extensive distribution of an EU special fund that has been
used to support its less developed members. Spain gets more than
half of the fund.
</P>
<P>
The leaders agreed that the EU should be open to all the
countries seeking for its membership in order to ward off "unfair"
treatment to some countries. 
</P>
