<HEADLINE> Rizhao Group of China Sets Up Office in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Rizhao Aquatic Product Group,
in east China's Shangdong Province, has recently opened an office
in Canada, the third one in North America.
</P>
<P>
The group, which has fixed assets of over 150 million yuan
(18.7 million US dollars), is mainly involved in the processing of
aquatic products and vegetables, deep-sea fishing, ship-building,
handicrafts manufacturing and the catering sector.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the group exported 5,700 tons of aquatic products,
earning over 32 million US dollars, accounting for 64 percent of
the city's total aquatic exports.
</P>
<P>
The Rizhao Group invested 15 million yuan in technological
renovations in 1996 as part of an effort to develop a niche in the
international market. As a result, all of its products have
fulfilled the world's quality standards.
</P>
<P>
The group has established 10 joint ventures with Japan, the
Republic of Korea, the United States, Singapore and some European
countries to process export-oriented aquatic products .
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
