<HEADLINE> Home-made Bomb Injures Three in Spain's Basque Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Three policemen were wounded by
a home-made bomb on Tuesday night when they tried to defuse the
device in Spain's Basque region.
</P>
<P>
The three police officers were bomb experts who were called in
to defuse the explosive outside the main entrance of a bank in San
Sebastian, officials said.
</P>
<P>
No group has claimed responsibility but police said the bomb
was apparently planted by armed group ETA fighting for an
independent Basque state.
</P>
<P>
The attack came one day after Spain's Supreme Court convicted
23 leaders of Herri Batasuna, a radical separatist party, for
collaborating with ETA.
</P>
<P>
The convicted would spend seven years in jail. 
