<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Continues to Weaken Against Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian currency of
rupiah continued to weaken Tuesday in the inter-bank spot market,
recording in a position of 3,815/35 against the U.S. dollar,
dealers said today.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah's closing position represented a decline of 100
points compared with Monday's closing of 3,715/30.
</P>
<P>
A weakening of regional (Southeast Asian) currencies appeared
to be the main factor behind the slump in the Indonesian
currency's value against the greenback, said the dealers.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian currency was under such pressure that its value
against the U.S. dollar slid into a position of 3.842 compared to
early trading when the market opened with the rupiah's value still
at 3,743/53 per dollar.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia, along with other Southeast Asian countries, has been
hit badly by the monetary crisis since early July. The value of
rupiah has dropped by more than 40 percent against the U.S. dollar
this year.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government has taken many measures to overcome
the monetary crisis. Indonesia received a long-term assistance of
23 billion U.S. dollars from the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
at the end the October.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
