<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Upgrades Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Qingyuan-Lianzhou Highway,
a 215.2-km category-A highway in south China's Guangdong
Province, has opened to traffic recently.
</P>
<P>
The four-lane highway, a section of the No.107 National
Highway, was upgraded to a width of 24.5 meters, Transport News
has reported.
</P>
<P>
The new highway now has a daily handling capacity of over 30,000
vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The project, completed at a cost of three billion yuan, will
significantly ease the transportation "bottleneck" in northwestern
Guangdong Province and will promote local economic growth,
according to local government officials.
</P>
<P>
The project, which commenced in autumn 1994, was mainly funded
by companies from Hong Kong and Singapore. 
</P>
