Mexico and a decisive 3-0 win over Canada and scored a 4-2 home
win over El Salvador, getting the second of three spots from the
North and Central American and Caribbean region to boost Sampson's
image.
</P>
<P>
Since taking over from Bora Milutinovic on April 14, 1995,
Sampson had led the Americans 20-11-16, and his .543 winning
percentage is the best among coaches of the U.S. team.
</P>
<P>
Sampson said he thought he could take the team "to the second
round, if not the third". 
