<HEADLINE> Peru's Exports Increase Markedly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Exports from Peru totaled 5.69
billion U.S. dollars in the first 10 months of this year, 18.4
percent more than in the same period of 1996, the Customs Office
of Peru said today.
</P>
<P>
Exports of traditional products from mining and fishing
amounted to 3.99 billion dollars from January to October of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Non-traditional product exports grew to 1.67 billion dollars, a
32.7 percent increase against the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The most dynamic non-traditional sector was metal products,
with a 70 percent growth and accumulated overseas sales of more
than 197 million dollars. 
