<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Herbal Medicine Enters US Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The United States Food and Drug
Administration (FDA), one of the world's strictest inspectors of
foodstuff and medicinal products, has granted "entry visas" to 21
Chinese herbal medicines, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Another 19 traditional Chinese medicines are currently in the
process of applying for import permits from the FDA, said an
official with the Academy of Traditional Chinese Medicine.
</P>
<P>
Medicines approved by the FDA are more likely to be accepted by
a number of other countries such as Canada, Mexico and Egypt,
according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The medicines allowed to enter the US market include tonics and
tablets to prevent and treat illnesses like colds, stomach-ache,
stroke and diarrhea. Some can help people's immune systems against
diseases such as cancer.
</P>
<P>
Data from the Academy of Traditional Chinese Medicine indicates
that about 600 million US dollars worth of traditional Chinese
medicine is exported each year. More than 70 percent of this is in
the form of raw medicinal herbs rather than finished products.
</P>
<P>
Most exports of traditional Chinese medicines go to Japan,
southeast Asian countries, and Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
the lack of an international standard, poor packaging and vague
instructions are major obstacles preventing Chinese herbal
medicines entering the world market, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971203.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA Cancels Yellow Cards For Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 2, (Xinhua) -- FIFA, the world soccer
governing body, Tuesday ruled that players will not carry yellow
cards from the World Cup qualification into next year's finals in
France.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's World Cup organising committee made this decision at
the World Cup draw ceremony held at Marseille, which decided the
eight seeded teams.
</P>
<P>
FIFA added that amnesty will not apply to red card offenders
in the finals whether they were directly sent off the field or
for two yellows.
</P>
<P>
The organising committee will still decide on the punishment
upon the Ukrainian international Sergei Nagorniak who was charged
with doping.
</P>
<P>
The doping of the international, who has been suspended by the
Ukraine Football Federation, was found out after the October 29
match between Croatia and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
FIFA meanwhile decided to award every football federation of
the 32 qualifiers 500,000 U.S. dollars and each team can get
714,000 U.S. dollars for every match.
</P>
<P>
The world soccer body conveyed the hope again that the host
France can remove all fences surrounding its 10 pitches for the
soccer premiere competition.
</P>
<P>
Of the ten venues for the competition, only Nantes' Le
Beaujoire and St Etienne's Geoffroy Guichard stadiums still have
fences and the authorities are yet to show their willingness to
wipe out the fences.
</P>
<P>
To avoid the repetition of the fan violence in the World Cup
playoff between England and Italy, the body hoped that tickets to
the fans through the unofficial channel should be strictly
controlled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
