<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Slips Against yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar Tuesday
slipped against the Japanese yen after Japan moved to defend its
currency, but it ended higher against most other major currencies.
</P>
<P>
Eisuke Sakakibara, Japan's vice minister for international
affairs, said his country is prepared to take action to defend
yen.
</P>
<P>
But traders still believe the long-term bullishness on the
dollar. The dollar was trading late Tuesday in New York at 128.64
yen, down from 128.91 yen late Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the dollar rose to 1.7782 German marks, from 1.7771
late Monday.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6807 U.S. dollars, down from
1.6846 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Other dollar rates in New York, compared with late Monday:
5.9490 French francs, up from 5.9475; 1.4335 Swiss francs, up from
1.4315; 1,740 Italian lire, down from 1,741; and 1.4195 Canadian
dollars, down from 1.4229.  
</P>
