<HEADLINE> Austrian City to Bid for 2006 Winter Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Australian city Klagenfurt won
the support of the Austrian Olympic Committee (AOG) on Tuesday for
a bid to host the 2006 Winter Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Salzburg and Kitzbuehel also tried to win the support from the
Austrian Olympic Committee for their bid for the games, but it was
Klagenfurt, capital of the province of Carinthia, which finally
got the go-ahead signal from the AOG.
</P>
