capital of Tajikistan, on November 30 with wounds sustained in an
armed operation to free her by the government security forces.
</P>
<P>
Praising Mane as one of the "selfless humanitarian workers who
defy the dangers inherent in crisis situations," Yasushi Akashi
said such hostage-taking practice should not be repeated in the
former Soviet republic as it has already happened twice. 
