<HEADLINE> Institute Set up to Help Cyprus' EU Accession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Institute of
Cyprus, an institute aimed at helping the preparation for Cyprus'
accession to the European Union (EU), opened today.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the Nicosia-based institute, visiting EU External
Relations Commissioner Hans Van den Broek, said that the opening
of the institute comes at a crucial moment of EU-Cyprus
relations, when accession negotiations for EU membership will
shortly start.
</P>
<P>
The EU commissioner, who is completing today his two-day visit
to the island, said the institute will "have a unique and
strategic mission to accomplish in the coming months to
contribute to the preparation of the Cypriot society in view of
the accession to the EU."
</P>
<P>
Cyprus Foreign Minister Ioanuis Kasoulides said that the
European Institute of Cyprus is an "achievement for all those
involved, as well as an important step for our country in its
effort to become an active member of the EU."
</P>
<P>
The newly-established institute will give the Cypriot public
an in-depth knowledge and understanding of the EU and its
development, history, institutions and functions.
</P>
<P>
It will also provide raw material for researchers,
journalists and officials about the EU.
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides said Cyprus must intensify its harmonization
efforts and finalize its internal institutional and economic
preparation for accession.
</P>
<P>
"We must do whatever is in our power, to achieve, by the time
of accession, a negotiated solution to the Cyprus problem, even
if the achievement of such a solution cannot be considered as a
precondition for accession," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot foreign minister said the institute will
participate in efforts to convince the Turkish Cypriots that
"the EU represents our common future."
</P>
<P>
Cyprus submitted in 1990 its application to the EU for full
membership. The EU decided in March 1995 that it will begin
accession talks with Cyprus early next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
