<HEADLINE> UK Shares Keep on Rising on Wall Street, Asian Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
ended mixed Tuesday, with London and Frankfurt extending Monday's
gains to finish firmer while Paris closing slightly lower.
</P>
<P>
British shares had languished for most of the day before
surging ahead in late trading, with the FTSE 100 index ending 55.8
points higher at 4,977.6.
</P>
<P>
The late spurt came as the Dow reversed initial weakness to
trade 20 points up when London market closed. Meanwhile, Asian
markets' steadiness after recent turbulence also supported the
market.
</P>
<P>
But the latest Bank of England monetary policy committee
meeting, due to end on Thursday, and Friday's release of US
non-farm payroll figures, both injected a note of caution.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index in Frankfurt lost almost all its early gains
after reaching a high of 4,111.62 to end just 4.91 points higher
at 4,072.96.
</P>
<P>
Profit-taking trimmed prices and gains were capped by the
slight softening in the dollar overnight.
</P>
<P>
However, the CAC-40 index closed down 5.39 points at 2,913.09.
Dealers said that share prices drifted lower as the market
consolidated on the back of a weaker dollar following Monday's
sharp gains.  
