<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Develop Telecommunication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's Telcom was
set to install a record 350,000 telephones this financial year,
the Department of Communications said today.
</P>
<P>
The previous record was 250,000 in 1996. Priority was being
given to under-serviced areas such as Kwazulu Natal Province and
Eastern Cape Province.
</P>
<P>
At least 421,000 new lines would have been installed by March
next year, 65 percent more than in 1996/1997, and 195 percent
more than in 1995/96.
</P>
<P>
Telcom would also install 120,000 public telephones in the
next five years, with a target of five public phones per 1,000
people in rural areas and 3.5 per 1,000 people in urban areas.
</P>
