<HEADLINE> UN Mission Goes to Britain For Lockerbie Air Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
today sent a three-person mission to Britain to assess the legal
system that would try two Libyans accused of blowing a Pan
American airliner over Lockerbie, Scotland, in 1988, UN
spokesman Fred Eckhard announced at the noon briefing.
</P>
<P>
Eckhard also announced that the United Nations would send
anther mission to Tripoli later this month to evaluate the
impact of UN sanctions on Libya.
</P>
<P>
Britain and the United States have accused the two alleged
Libyan intelligence agents of blowing the Pal American airliner
which killed 270 people.
</P>
<P>
Libya has been under UN air, arms and diplomatic sanctions
since 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
